cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.SD, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper analyzes the attention and popularity of YouTube videos, which are part of a social network. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper uses information theoretical measures to examine the popularity of videos. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper focuses on videos on YouTube. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper may discuss the algorithms and software used by YouTube to promote popular videos. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also less likely but possible as the paper may discuss how users interact with and consume YouTube videos.
